Description:
Location: East Croydon
Role: Full-time
Hours: 40 hours per week
Start Date: Immediate
COMPANY
Green Network Energy is a new independent energy and gas supplier in the UK for domestic and business customer.
The company is part of an Italian Group Green Network Spa based in Rome since 2003. Today is a top 10 Independent energy company in Europe with annual revenues of over €2billion.
As a company with big ambitions to grow, we are looking to recruit new talent to be part of our journey.
ROLE
This role offers an excellent opportunity to work in an exciting and growing energy supply company, where you will be integral part of our Customer service team! Your role will be to support the team with all data protection related queries and tasks and you will work closely with our Data Protection Adviser. Ideally, you will be a driven and engaged individual, who is motivated by challenges. You will also have a good level of knowledge of the energy industry. '
RESPONSIBILITIES
· Logging and tracking all data protection related queries;
· Conducting research and following legal and regulatory updates related to data protection- in the UK, EU and globally);
· Handling data subject requests, particularly data deletion and access requests, ensuring relevant processes are always followed.
· Supporting incident reporting and data breach investigations;
· Supporting the completion of privacy risk assessments, including data inventories; records of processing activities; privacy assessments; DPIAs;
· Keeping all data protection related documentation up to date;
Help identifying risks, requirements to improve existing practices relevant to data protection;
Supporting the delivery of data protection trainings to all staff;
Supporting the Data Protection Adviser and the CIO on data protection and information security related tasks, where required;
Supporting Customer care team with their day-to-day activities, when necessary.
*
SKILLS & EXPERIENCE
A good understanding of UK and EU Data Protection laws, in particular the Data Protection Act 2018 and the GDPR;
Relevant experience in a similar role, preferably in the energy sector;
Excellent organisational, time management and communication skills;
Eager to learn;
Able to manage and work to strict deadlines;
Excellent verbal and written skills with the ability to show attention to detail;
· Conflict resolution and strong communications skills;
Innovate, create solutions, and engage with colleagues and customers in a friendly professional way.
BENEFITS
· Competitive Salary
· Complementary hot drinks (coffee machines everywhere!)
· Game Area (table tennis and foosball table)
· Employee Preferred Tariff if you become our Customer (discounted gas and electricity bills)
· Discounts for gym
· Employee Cash Plan
GNE is a diverse and inclusive employer. We celebrate diversity. We are committed to build a team that reflects a wide variety of skills, background, and cultures. No applicant will be treated less favourably on the grounds of their sex, marital or civil partnership status, race, nationality or ethnic origin, disability, sexual orientation, gender identity, gender reassignment, pregnancy, maternity, age, religion or belief. Applicants may be subject to a basic Disclosure and Barring Service check and at least two independent references.
